    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6587" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ξίφος</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">sword.</span> The <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ξίφος</span> had a two-edged blade, joined to the hilt (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κώπη</span>) by bands of dark metal (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μελάνδετον</span>). It was worn in a sheath
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κουλεόν</span>), suspended by a baldric
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τελαμών</span>) that passed over the
          shoulder. (See cut on preceding page.)</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
